26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_i2c_padg94.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "pad.h"
30#include "aux.h"
31#include "bus.h"
32
33void
34g94_i2c_pad_mode(struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad, enum nvkm_i2c_pad_mode mode)
35{
36 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &pad->i2c->subdev;
37 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
38 const u32 base = (pad->id - NVKM_I2C_PAD_HYBRID(0)) * 0x50;
39
40 switch (mode) {
41 case NVKM_I2C_PAD_OFF:
42 nvkm_mask(device, 0x00e50c + base, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
43 break;
44 case NVKM_I2C_PAD_I2C:
45 nvkm_mask(device, 0x00e500 + base, 0x0000c003, 0x0000c001);
46 nvkm_mask(device, 0x00e50c + base, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
47 break;
48 case NVKM_I2C_PAD_AUX:
49 nvkm_mask(device, 0x00e500 + base, 0x0000c003, 0x00000002);
50 nvkm_mask(device, 0x00e50c + base, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
51 break;
52 default:
53 WARN_ON(1);
54 break;
55 }
56}
57
58static const struct nvkm_i2c_pad_func
59g94_i2c_pad_s_func = {
60 .bus_new_4 = nv50_i2c_bus_new,
61 .aux_new_6 = g94_i2c_aux_new,
62 .mode = g94_i2c_pad_mode,
63};
64
65int
66g94_i2c_pad_s_new(struct nvkm_i2c *i2c, int id, struct nvkm_i2c_pad **ppad)
67{
68 return nvkm_i2c_pad_new_(&g94_i2c_pad_s_func, i2c, id, ppad);
69}
70
71static const struct nvkm_i2c_pad_func
72g94_i2c_pad_x_func = {
73 .bus_new_4 = nv50_i2c_bus_new,
74 .aux_new_6 = g94_i2c_aux_new,
75};
76
77int
78g94_i2c_pad_x_new(struct nvkm_i2c *i2c, int id, struct nvkm_i2c_pad **ppad)
79{
80 return nvkm_i2c_pad_new_(&g94_i2c_pad_x_func, i2c, id, ppad);
81}
